100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 18, 1926, the League of Nations in Geneva addressed increasing tensions in Europe, particularly regarding disarmament discussions among member nations. In the United States, the Senate continued deliberations on the controversial McNary-Haugen Bill, which aimed to support farmers by stabilizing prices for agricultural products. Meanwhile, in Chicago, a significant blizzard disrupted transportation and daily life, prompting local authorities to implement emergency measures.
